I think, we must use separate logic to create typeface for these fonts (Univers 45 Light & TraditionSansXLight)

```
SKTypeFace.FromFamilyName("Univers 45", SKFontStyleWeight.Light, SKFontStyleWidth.Normal, SKFontStyleSlant.Upright)
SKTypeface.FromFamilyName("TraditionSansXLight", SKFontStyleWeight.Light, SKFontStyleWidth.Normal, SKFontStyleSlant.Upright);
```

I have used below code to achieve this. Please let me know, if you have any other solution.

```
string fontName = "TraditionSansXLight"; //Or "Univers 45 Light",etc.
SKTypeface typeFace = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(fontName, SKFontStyleWeight.Light, SKFontStyleWidth.Normal, SKFontStyleSlant.Upright);
if(typeFace.FamilyName != fontName && fontName.Contains("Light"))
{
        fontName = fontName.Replace("Light", string.Empty).Trim();
        typeFace = SKTypeface.FromFamilyName(fontName, SKFontStyleWeight.Light, SKFontStyleWidth.Normal, SKFontStyleSlant.Upright);
}
```
